1
00:01:31,013 --> 00:01:34,317
Long-range magic is a fickle
thing and rather difficult to master.

2
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:38,822
Success requires a combination of three key
factors that are essential to all mages.

3
00:01:39,543 --> 00:01:45,150
There's the amount of mana utilized, the strength at which
it's fired, and the level of control you have over it.

4
00:01:45,650 --> 00:01:46,930
But you know that much, correct?

5
00:01:47,548 --> 00:01:48,548
Yes.

6
00:01:48,929 --> 00:01:51,691
Earlier, your magic dissipated
before it reached its target.

7
00:01:52,251 --> 00:01:55,533
That tells me your levels of mana
and your firing strength are both lacking.

8
00:01:56,454 --> 00:01:58,635
These are not issues
that one can fix overnight.

9
00:01:59,556 --> 00:02:03,118
Regardless of your talent, such
skills will take years to master.

10
00:02:08,398 --> 00:02:12,644
That said, the level of control you
have over your magic is very high.

11
00:02:13,144 --> 00:02:18,011
That's the area where most people tend to struggle,
but you're already exhibiting great strength there.

12
00:02:18,612 --> 00:02:20,614
My advice is to be patient with yourself.

13
00:02:23,578 --> 00:02:24,578
All right.

14
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:49,828
Frieren, Himmel, Heiter, Eisen, Flamme, Serie, Denken,
Übel, Land, Wirbel, Richter, Kanne, Lawine, Draht, Solitär.

15
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:36,696
Is Fern's training coming along smoothly?

16
00:03:37,657 --> 00:03:40,820
In a short four years, she's
learned more than most do in ten.

17
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,761
I don't feel this is a good thing.

18
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:44,422
She is studying too hard.

19
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:45,603
Perhaps.

20
00:03:45,964 --> 00:03:48,005
Nothing seems to pull her out of the woods.

21
00:03:48,506 --> 00:03:51,388
Even so, I'm glad she's
found something she loves.

22
00:03:51,848 --> 00:03:54,871
Regardless, she's still a long
way from becoming a proper mage.

23
00:03:55,511 --> 00:03:58,373
I'll have deciphered the grimoire
before she reaches that status.

24
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:00,614
Is that so?

25
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:10,882
You know, Heiter, the odds this text
contains anything pertaining to... Heiter?

26
00:04:18,886 --> 00:04:21,327
You can wipe that
look of pity off your face.

27
00:04:22,087 --> 00:04:25,868
I consider the fact I stayed on
my feet for so long a minor miracle.

28
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,911
I will try to be quick with my work.

29
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:34,107
Thank you, my friend.

30
00:04:39,849 --> 00:04:41,789
Fern, I need you with Heiter.

31
00:04:42,389 --> 00:04:43,389
He collapsed.

32
00:04:43,570 --> 00:04:44,806
Put your training on hold.

33
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:48,511
But I still haven't shot
through the boulder.

34
00:04:49,911 --> 00:04:52,052
I have no doubt you'll
achieve it eventually.

35
00:04:52,592 --> 00:04:54,608
Right now, we— It cannot be eventually!

36
00:04:54,632 --> 00:05:01,094
When eventually comes, Master
Heiter will have passed away.

37
00:05:04,698 --> 00:05:12,698
Man saved my life, you know.

38
00:05:18,550 --> 00:05:21,493
Throwing away your life
now would be an utter waste.

39
00:05:22,854 --> 00:05:23,875
A waste, mister?

40
00:05:25,236 --> 00:05:27,518
A long time ago, I lost someone too.

41
00:05:28,599 --> 00:05:31,122
He was a dear companion
whom I cherished very much.

42
00:05:32,242 --> 00:05:35,024
His heart was made of gold
and his nerves made of steel.

43
00:05:35,344 --> 00:05:39,207
He would sooner sacrifice his
life than abandon someone in need.

44
00:05:40,848 --> 00:05:46,231
If he was still here, and I was the one six feet
below, more innocent lives could have been saved.

45
00:05:47,512 --> 00:05:52,995
Since I'm not the type for such selflessness, I
planned to live out the rest of my days quietly.

46
00:05:53,336 --> 00:05:56,618
But before I could hole up
for good, I realized something.

47
00:05:57,577 --> 00:06:05,577
If I sat and died in silence, all I learned about friendship, strength of will, and
courage, all the precious memories we had made, they would vanish like they had never been.

48
00:06:12,064 --> 00:06:20,064
If there is even one precious memory tucked within the walls
of your mind, then I think it would be a waste for you to die.

49
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:26,812
Master Heiter fears dying now more
than ever, because it means I'll be alone.

50
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:30,841
I have to show him he did
the right thing back then.

51
00:06:31,901 --> 00:06:33,943
Saving my life can't be his final regret.

52
00:06:35,204 --> 00:06:37,526
I don't care if it's as a
mage or whatever else.

53
00:06:37,846 --> 00:06:41,529
Learning some kind of skill to support
myself is my way of repaying him.

54
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:47,353
He's the reason I'm here, and I need
him to know I'll be alright when he's gone.

55
00:06:51,256 --> 00:06:53,577
Do you remember everything
that I've taught you so far?

56
00:06:54,538 --> 00:06:55,538
Yes.

57
00:06:55,699 --> 00:06:55,939
Good.

58
00:06:56,219 --> 00:06:57,219
Then do as you like.

59
00:07:18,663 --> 00:07:19,663
Scherzo.

60
00:07:58,542 --> 00:08:02,043
There weren't any spells for bringing
back the dead or granting immortality.

61
00:08:02,784 --> 00:08:03,784
Worth a try.

62
00:08:04,344 --> 00:08:05,344
Did you know that?

63
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:09,126
An immeasurable fear
of death lives within us all.

64
00:08:09,626 --> 00:08:13,728
If such spells did exist, Eivig most
surely would have cast them on himself.

65
00:08:14,548 --> 00:08:15,548
Then why bother?

66
00:08:17,229 --> 00:08:17,969
How's Frieren?

67
00:08:18,129 --> 00:08:19,270
Is she growing strong?

68
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:25,352
She has room to improve in some areas, but it
wouldn't be incorrect to call her a proper mage.

69
00:08:27,453 --> 00:08:27,933
Excellent.

70
00:08:28,314 --> 00:08:29,795
So she made it in time.

71
00:08:31,476 --> 00:08:34,677
It'll be hard for you to say she'll
get in your way, now, won't it?

72
00:08:37,199 --> 00:08:39,901
Will you bring her with you
and strengthen her skills?

73
00:08:40,841 --> 00:08:43,383
Forgive me, Heiter, but I must draw a line.

74
00:08:44,704 --> 00:08:46,024
She would only get in my way.

75
00:08:47,045 --> 00:08:48,666
You deceived me, didn't you?

76
00:08:52,288 --> 00:08:55,150
Your payment for decrypting
the grimoire is in the desk.

77
00:08:56,415 --> 00:08:58,596
I must ask you to leave this place tonight.

78
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:00,497
For what reason?

79
00:09:01,898 --> 00:09:05,200
I'm sure you can see that I'm
not much longer for this world.

80
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:12,844
At such a young age, that child has already experienced
more than enough loss to last the rest of her lifetime.

81
00:09:14,104 --> 00:09:17,366
Frieren, please take care of Fern for me.

82
00:09:20,008 --> 00:09:21,808
No point in feigning courage again.

83
00:09:22,109 --> 00:09:23,109
Not now.

84
00:09:25,865 --> 00:09:28,746
She has been ready to say
goodbye to you for a long while.

85
00:09:29,807 --> 00:09:37,807
Your only focus before you die should be giving her a
proper farewell and making as many memories as you can.

86
00:09:42,173 --> 00:09:46,455
Oh, Frieren, you really are a kind girl.

87
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:59,346
So, why did you save Fern?

88
00:10:16,435 --> 00:10:19,593
Because that is what Himmel,
the hero, would have done.

89
00:10:19,617 --> 00:10:23,059
You're right.

90
00:10:36,884 --> 00:10:37,985
A good guiding voice.

91
00:10:39,685 --> 00:10:40,986
Perhaps I'll listen as well.

92
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,090
I really can't thank you enough.

93
00:10:54,011 --> 00:10:57,752
Without your help and guidance, I
couldn't have repaid Master Heiter.

94
00:10:59,337 --> 00:11:01,620
Then you should be
thanking him for deceiving me.

95
00:11:03,502 --> 00:11:05,104
So long, corrupt priest.

96
00:11:10,871 --> 00:11:12,153
Well, shall we be off?

97
00:11:34,868 --> 00:11:35,868
Stop there, Fern.

98
00:11:36,488 --> 00:11:40,409
That's plenty.

99
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:43,250
Thank you kindly for your help.

100
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:45,571
As for your payment, take this.

101
00:11:47,871 --> 00:11:50,052
We've been doing such simple work lately.

102
00:11:50,532 --> 00:11:52,393
Thus is the nature of adventuring.

103
00:11:53,153 --> 00:11:54,753
What did we get paid in this time?

104
00:11:55,093 --> 00:11:56,093
More folk magic.

105
00:11:56,474 --> 00:11:58,354
It's a spell that produces warm tea.

106
00:11:58,734 --> 00:12:00,054
We'll have to try this out later.

107
00:12:02,031 --> 00:12:05,453
The other day we learned a spell
that cleans rust from bronze statues.

108
00:12:06,313 --> 00:12:09,414
And before that, there was the
one for turning sweet grapes sour.

109
00:12:11,455 --> 00:12:13,656
You keep collecting the strangest spells.

110
00:12:14,057 --> 00:12:15,297
That is my hobby.

111
00:12:16,117 --> 00:12:19,399
It sounds to me like you really
do love magic, Mistress Frieren.

112
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:20,739
Only somewhat.

113
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:21,816
The same as you.

114
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:25,242
I, uh, feel we're a bit different.

115
00:12:27,183 --> 00:12:28,183
We're the same.

116
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:32,873
You're absolutely sure you
wouldn't mind doing me a favor?

117
00:12:33,895 --> 00:12:38,235
As an herbalist, I can't say I have
any spells to teach you in return.

118
00:12:38,259 --> 00:12:39,781
That's alright.

119
00:12:40,602 --> 00:12:43,645
Any information we can learn
on local flora is helpful enough.

120
00:12:48,391 --> 00:12:49,391
There he is.

121
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,822
A statue of Himmel the Hero.

122
00:12:57,382 --> 00:12:59,644
The poor boy is in terrible shape.

123
00:13:00,245 --> 00:13:03,608
I would clean him myself, but
it's too much for one old lady.

124
00:13:04,569 --> 00:13:06,991
And I can't convince
the other villagers to care.

125
00:13:30,523 --> 00:13:36,368
When the village was attacked by a vicious monster, the
brave Mr. Himmel fought with all his might to defend us.

126
00:13:37,249 --> 00:13:39,851
Such a hero should be
revered, not left to crumble.

127
00:13:41,193 --> 00:13:42,193
Perhaps.

128
00:13:42,774 --> 00:13:44,075
But not in Himmel's case.

129
00:13:44,696 --> 00:13:46,818
It's only fair that he pays for his pride.

130
00:13:47,738 --> 00:13:51,582
When the villagers offered to make a statue
of him, he should have humbly declined.

131
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,000
How is this?

132
00:13:55,081 --> 00:13:56,722
You don't think it's too handsome, right?

133
00:13:56,902 --> 00:14:01,385
He spent 18 hours choosing a
pose, driving the poor sculptor mad.

134
00:14:02,446 --> 00:14:06,348
All of that debate, and they settled
on something ridiculously ordinary.

135
00:14:07,789 --> 00:14:09,170
I've never heard that before.

136
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:15,154
Come to think of it, there was an elven
mage in the hero's party, wasn't there?

137
00:14:17,015 --> 00:14:18,456
So, shall we clean him up?

138
00:14:22,896 --> 00:14:24,196
Thank you so much.

139
00:14:24,997 --> 00:14:26,717
Magic is an incredible thing.

140
00:14:27,137 --> 00:14:29,438
There isn't a speck of
rust anywhere in sight.

141
00:14:31,999 --> 00:14:34,619
I do wish there was a bit
more color around here, though.

142
00:14:34,939 --> 00:14:36,840
I'll have to plant some flowers soon.

143
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,700
We could do that.

144
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:41,161
You have a spell that
produces flowers, don't you?

145
00:14:41,781 --> 00:14:42,538
Yes, indeed.

146
00:14:42,562 --> 00:14:44,762
I suppose I could conjure something.

147
00:14:48,343 --> 00:14:51,124
No, blue moon weed flowers would be best.

148
00:14:51,678 --> 00:14:52,819
I can't recall that one.

149
00:14:52,859 --> 00:14:53,859
What do they look like?

150
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:54,680
I don't know.

151
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,160
I've never seen them.

152
00:14:56,661 --> 00:14:57,661
Then why those?

153
00:14:58,282 --> 00:15:00,083
Because they grow in Himmel's hometown.

154
00:15:00,884 --> 00:15:03,165
You can't conjure flowers
you haven't seen before.

155
00:15:10,430 --> 00:15:11,630
Blue Moonweed.

156
00:15:12,331 --> 00:15:13,992
Haven't heard that name in years.

157
00:15:16,987 --> 00:15:21,630
Long ago, a beautiful lush field of them
used to bloom right outside my house.

158
00:15:27,813 --> 00:15:29,214
So they don't grow here anymore?

159
00:15:30,855 --> 00:15:32,356
Seems they died off on us.

160
00:15:33,276 --> 00:15:36,938
It's been several decades now since
they were last spotted in these lands.

161
00:15:42,882 --> 00:15:44,422
Fern, let's go.

162
00:15:44,963 --> 00:15:45,963
Coming.

163
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,533
You're hiding something.

164
00:15:52,853 --> 00:15:54,534
Whatever it is, I won't be upset.

165
00:15:58,955 --> 00:15:59,995
Found friends, did you?

166
00:16:00,755 --> 00:16:02,075
I believe they're seed rats.

167
00:16:02,855 --> 00:16:03,895
I'll take them outside.

168
00:16:09,196 --> 00:16:12,097
Well, Fern, shall our moon
weed quest commence?

169
00:16:12,757 --> 00:16:14,057
Are you joking, Mistress?

170
00:16:15,097 --> 00:16:16,097
Why would I be?

171
00:16:16,258 --> 00:16:17,954
She said there was a
field of them right here.

172
00:16:17,978 --> 00:16:18,978
Decades ago.

173
00:16:19,625 --> 00:16:21,186
But they're well worth looking for.

174
00:16:22,707 --> 00:16:27,749
If we're able to find and analyze them, we
can conjure Blue Moon Weed wherever we like.

175
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:30,671
You're doing this for Himmel's sake?

176
00:16:31,651 --> 00:16:32,651
Oh no.

177
00:16:32,932 --> 00:16:34,413
I believe I'm doing it for my own.

178
00:17:27,801 --> 00:17:31,403
Mistress Frieren, we've scoured
these woods for six months.

179
00:17:31,823 --> 00:17:33,363
I don't think we're going to find it.

180
00:17:33,883 --> 00:17:34,883
You're right.

181
00:17:34,924 --> 00:17:37,405
Perhaps it's time we broaden
the radius of our quest.

182
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:50,191
Oh, I don't often see you on your own.

183
00:17:53,111 --> 00:17:56,432
It's been quite a while since
you two first arrived in this village.

184
00:17:58,152 --> 00:18:00,413
So, have you found any Blue Moon Weed?

185
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:03,034
Is our search a lost cause?

186
00:18:05,494 --> 00:18:08,635
She's so quick to fixate on
anything relating to magic.

187
00:18:09,675 --> 00:18:13,756
By the looks of it, she's going to continue
this hunt for years, if not decades.

188
00:18:15,143 --> 00:18:18,904
Given her strength as a mage, she has
the power to save whole cities of people.

189
00:18:20,604 --> 00:18:23,185
She shouldn't spend her time
looking for something so tiny.

190
00:18:23,825 --> 00:18:25,265
Something that may not exist.

191
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:28,486
You're so young, child.

192
00:18:30,386 --> 00:18:32,987
Is that simply a polite way
of saying you think I'm wrong?

193
00:18:34,247 --> 00:18:36,408
No, and I don't disagree with you.

194
00:18:37,428 --> 00:18:41,389
But you see, Miss Frieren likely
views things differently than you and me.

195
00:18:44,526 --> 00:18:49,210
And because she's so much more mature than
us, I'm sure she'd understand your feelings.

196
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:53,713
If you say how you feel with an open
heart, I've no doubt she'll take it well.

197
00:19:12,887 --> 00:19:16,510
They're the seeds of a related species
she kept for their medicinal properties.

198
00:19:17,911 --> 00:19:21,334
Would it be alright if we planted
these around Himmel's statue instead?

199
00:19:22,595 --> 00:19:23,596
I hear you, Fern.

200
00:19:24,717 --> 00:19:26,218
And I see I've made you worry.

201
00:19:29,741 --> 00:19:32,103
The time I spend isn't
solely my own anymore.

202
00:19:32,984 --> 00:19:33,984
We should go.

203
00:19:35,005 --> 00:19:36,847
I promise that I'll end my search soon.

204
00:19:39,735 --> 00:19:42,072
Mistress, how many years is soon?

205
00:19:42,096 --> 00:19:43,776
Ah, soon enough.

206
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:45,917
Please, no.

207
00:19:45,997 --> 00:19:53,997
That's not comforting, coming-Shhh.

208
00:19:59,162 --> 00:20:00,442
Shall we see where it's heading?

209
00:20:31,135 --> 00:20:34,898
I've been wanting to ask, why do
you collect spells in the first place?

210
00:20:35,339 --> 00:20:36,660
It's just a hobby of mine.

211
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:38,241
That's quite hard to believe.

212
00:20:39,382 --> 00:20:40,744
It's a hobby, and a good one.

213
00:20:42,185 --> 00:20:45,408
I used to go through my life much
more apathetically before finding it.

214
00:21:11,535 --> 00:21:12,535
Gross.

215
00:21:21,539 --> 00:21:24,661
But then came a fool who
praised me for the magic I acquired.

216
00:21:25,361 --> 00:21:26,401
The rest is history.

217
00:21:28,863 --> 00:21:30,343
That's a pretty silly reason.

218
00:21:31,464 --> 00:21:32,464
I agree.

219
00:21:54,848 --> 00:21:57,049
Is that... A flower petal.

220
00:21:58,350 --> 00:22:02,712
They say seed rats store their food by burying
it in safe places away from their enemies.

221
00:22:03,753 --> 00:22:05,594
They're clever little critters, aren't they?

222
00:22:06,714 --> 00:22:07,714
I wouldn't say that.

223
00:22:08,795 --> 00:22:13,018
They bury their food all over, so they
often forget where they hide their reserves.

224
00:22:18,380 --> 00:22:19,461
Blue Moonweed?

225
00:22:19,841 --> 00:22:21,362
A flower grown in my homeland.

226
00:22:22,142 --> 00:22:23,503
They're truly beautiful.

227
00:22:24,452 --> 00:22:26,753
To be fair, they grow pretty heroes too.

228
00:22:27,193 --> 00:22:28,273
Shall we get going then?

229
00:22:29,914 --> 00:22:33,394
Frieren, I'd like to show you them someday.

230
00:22:35,275 --> 00:22:37,276
Sure, if the chance arises.

231
00:22:46,098 --> 00:22:49,559
I had a feeling we'd find them
here, but I wasn't expecting this.

232
00:22:54,296 --> 00:22:55,556
Seems the chance arose.

233
00:22:56,196 --> 00:22:57,196
At last.

234
00:23:02,478 --> 00:23:04,678
I can't believe that
we actually found them.

235
00:23:05,419 --> 00:23:07,979
Now we can create a spell
to conjure Blue Moon Weed.

236
00:23:08,959 --> 00:23:11,400
It's evident how important magic is to you.

237
00:23:12,380 --> 00:23:13,560
I don't understand why.

238
00:23:14,541 --> 00:23:15,541
Yes, you do.

239
00:23:16,601 --> 00:23:20,122
Becoming a mage was a challenge,
but you never once wanted to give up.

240
00:23:21,934 --> 00:23:22,994
That's very different.

241
00:23:23,814 --> 00:23:28,291
I could have learned any other skill that allowed
me to support myself and been just as content.

242
00:23:28,315 --> 00:23:31,296
It didn't have to be magic.

243
00:23:32,436 --> 00:23:33,436
No.

244
00:23:34,097 --> 00:23:35,457
But it's what you chose.

245
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:48,700
I guess you're right.

246
00:23:51,287 --> 00:23:52,448
Blue Mood Weed.

247
00:23:53,388 --> 00:23:55,089
I thought I would never see it again.

248
00:23:56,029 --> 00:23:57,430
It looks beautiful.

249
00:23:59,131 --> 00:24:01,212
Thank you for your diligence, Miss Frieren.

250
00:24:01,732 --> 00:24:05,110
You've ensured that time will never
get the better of the statue again.

251
00:24:05,134 --> 00:24:08,552
Oh, I nearly forgot.

252
00:24:08,576 --> 00:24:10,737
There.

253
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:13,317
Look at that!

254
00:24:13,738 --> 00:24:15,239
An adorable touch.

255
00:24:16,099 --> 00:24:17,580
Well, shall we be off?

